annotationA: GPI inositol-deacylase; Involved in inositol deacylation of GPI-anchored proteins
annotationB: Phosphatidylinositol glycan anchor biosynthesis, class U is a subunit of glycosylphosphatidylinositol (GPI) transamidase, which mediates GPI anchoring in the endoplasmic reticulum. GPI anchor attachment serves as a general mechanism for linking proteins to the cell surface membrane
